Investment Process
Investment Philosophy







Comprehensive& Responsive 




 







Investment Process
Goal: Construct portfolio to provide return objectives while minimizing risks

We work to provide our clients with these key benefits:
Maintain control of your financial future
Reduce the amount of time to manage your wealth
Select investments most likely to help achieve your objectives
Accommodate risk tolerance level and any unique constraints
Control investment expenses
Effectively manage tax liability
Stay abreast of new investment developments and products
Update your investment strategy as appropriate
Reduce unnecessary investment risks
 

 



 




Evaluate Current Goals and Objectives
Working closely with you, we will assess your current financial condition and objectives, as well as your risk tolerance. We will develop a long-term strategy designed to align with your objectives and risk parameters.
Develop Investment Policy
We will prepare a personalized Invesment Policy Statement (IPS), complete with expected rate of return targets, allocation guidelines, liquidity needs and rebalancing procedures. Ongoing investment decisions are based on the IPS, and its appropriateness will be reviewed on a regular basis.
Implement Portfolio Design
Modera will recommend specific strategies and investments to implement your asset allocation plan. We consider the optimal tax location of each investment if you have tax-deferred and taxable accounts. We also factor in possible capital gains or losses. The execution strategy will depend on specific asset allocation as well as liquidity, tax, cost and other considerations that have been reviewed in the planning process.
Manage Portfolio
Once the portfolio design is implemented, we will work to control risk by monitoring the underlying investments and periodically rebalancing to the target asset class weight. Rebalancing occurs on the basis of how far markets have moved the portolio allocation from the target. We utilize robust portfolio management and rebalancing technologies that allow for the monitoring and oversight of all portfolio holdings and their allocations for the assets we manage.
Measure and Report Results
Periodic reviews of needs, circumstances, and requirements are critical to help an investment plan succeed. On a quarterly basis, we will provide you with a succinct analysis of the performance and risk of your portfolio. You also will receive monthly account statements and transaction confirmations from the independent custodian holding your accounts. 




 
 
 



